# Shadcn styling

Use shadcn semantic tokens and components. Do not hardcode palette classes.

## Do not use

- `bg-[#…]`, `bg-black`, `bg-white` (except shadcn overlay defaults in `components/ui/`)
- `bg-zinc-*`, `text-zinc-*`, `border-zinc-*`, `bg-gray-*`, `text-gray-*`
- `bg-amber-*`, `text-amber-*` for CTAs or accents (use `primary` tokens)
- Color overrides on shadcn primitives (`Input`, `DialogContent`, `Select`, `Button`)

## Use instead

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| `bg-[#0c0c0c]` | `bg-background` |
| `text-zinc-100/200` | `text-foreground` |
| `text-zinc-400/500/600` | `text-muted-foreground` |
| `border-zinc-700/800` | `border-border` |
| `bg-zinc-900/30` | `bg-card` or `bg-muted/40` |
| `bg-amber-600` CTAs | `<Button>` (default → `bg-primary`) |
| `text-red-400` errors | `text-destructive` |
| Secondary surfaces | `bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground` |

## Prefer shadcn components

Use `<Button variant="outline|secondary|ghost">`, `<Badge>`, `<Input>`, `<Dialog>` without custom color classes. Fix theme tokens in `globals.css` if contrast is wrong.

## Example

```tsx
// BAD
<li className="border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-3 bg-zinc-900/30">
  <p className="text-sm text-zinc-300">Note</p>
  <button className="bg-amber-600 text-black">Save</button>
</li>

// GOOD
<li className="border border-border rounded-lg p-3 bg-card">
  <p className="text-sm text-foreground">Note</p>
  <Button>Save</Button>
</li>
```
